.TH "bio_copy_kern" 9 "bio_copy_kern" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bio_copy_kern \- copy kernel address into bio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct bio *" bio_copy_kern
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ","
.BI "int reading "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
the struct request_queue for the bio
.IP "data" 12
pointer to buffer to copy
.IP "len" 12
length in bytes
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
allocation flags for bio and page allocation
.IP "reading" 12
data direction is READ

copy the kernel address into a bio suitable for io to a block
device. Returns an error pointer in case of error.
